						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Great Hierophant wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Update:<br /><br /><strong>The PowerPak with Mapper v1.00 passess all blargg's tests except for #5! (MMC1A)</strong></div>
<br />Don't worry about the MMC3 Revision A test - that will always fail since RevB is the preferred implementation (there are a couple of games that rely on RevB behavior, but not on RevA behavior AFAIK).  Without support for NES 2.0 or some other enhanced detection, RevB will always be the way the PowerPak will be configured.
<br />
<br />I find it odd that the scanline test is the only one that passes.  Most (if not all) games only need that test to pass to work properly.  How sensitive is the timing in that test?  If you're off by one or two cycles, will that test still pass?</div>

					
